- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper specifically focuses on ultrasound and acoustic data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the data was collected from child speech therapy sessions, which could involve social interactions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper mentions automatic annotations, which could involve machine learning techniques. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possibility as the software tools provided are meant to aid in the analysis and visualization of the data, which could involve human-computer interaction.
